3.1.1 Getting the tools
-----------------------

If you want to build R from the sources, you will first need to
collect, install and test an extensive set of tools.  See *Note The
Windows toolset:: (and perhaps updates in
`http://www.murdoch-sutherland.com/Rtools/') for details.

   The `Rtools.exe' executable installer described in *Note The Windows
toolset:: also includes some source files in addition to the R source
as noted below. You should run it first, to obtain a working `tar' and
other necessities.  Choose a "Full installation", and install the extra
files into your intended R source directory, e.g.  `C:/R'. The
directory name _should not contain spaces_. We will call this directory
R_HOME below.


