A.3.1.2 ACML
............

For `x86_64' and `i686' processors under Linux and Solaris 10 there is
the AMD Core Math Library (ACML) `http://www.amd.com/acml'.  For the
`gcc' version we could use

     --with-blas="-lacml"

if the appropriate library directory (such as `/opt/acml4.3.0/gfortran64/lib')
is in the `LD_LIBRRARY_PATH'.  For other compilers, see the ACML
documentation.  There is a multithreaded Linux version of ACML
available for `gfortran' which needs `gcc' >= 4.2.0 (or some RedHat
versions of 4.1.x).  To make use of this you will need something like

     --with-blas="-L/opt/acml4.3.0/gfortran64_mp/lib -lacml_mp"

   See *note Shared BLAS:: for an alternative (and in many ways
preferable) way to use ACML.


