C.4 Mac OS X
============

You can build R as a Unix application on Mac OS X using the Apple
Developer Tools (`Xcode') and `gfortran'.  You will also need to
install an X sub-system or configure with `--without-x'.  The X window
manager is part of the standard Mac OS X distribution since Mac OS X
version 10.3 (Panther), but it is typically not pre-installed prior to
10.5 (Leopard).

   For more information on how to find these tools please read the R
for Mac OS X FAQ
(http://CRAN.R-project.org/bin/macosx/RMacOSX-FAQ.html).

   The `vecLib' library can be used _via_ the (default) configuration
options

     --with-blas="-framework vecLib" --with-lapack

to provide higher-performance versions of the BLAS and LAPACK routines.
Building R without these options _via_

     --without-blas --without-lapack

can be done (and is provided as an alternative in the binary
distribution).

